{
  "$comment": "SHARED GOLDEN WIRE-FORMAT VECTORS (testing-guide T-5, §2.2). Hand-transcribed from the authoritative RFC texts and NEVER regenerated from our own implementation -- a vector produced by the code under test would only assert that the code agrees with itself. Adding or changing a vector requires a change to ai-docs/05-operation-log.md or ai-docs/testing-guide.md FIRST (T-5). Consumed by packages/core/test/jcs-vectors (Node, CI stage 5), the Hermes vector runner (CI stage 6), the noble interop suite (CI stage 7) and, on device, quick-crypto (CI stage 12).",
  "$security": "NOT SECRETS. Every key material below is a PUBLIC, published test value: the Ed25519 seeds are the RFC 8032 §7.1 test vectors and the argon2id inputs are the RFC 9106 §5.3 constants (repeated 01/02/03/04 bytes). They exist so two implementations can be proven byte-identical. They MUST never be used outside tests, and no production key may ever be added to this file.",
